            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "@bodograumann Yeah, I think that makes sense, but the real takeaway here is that we probably could benefit from more comprehensive test cases to be defined explicitly. I doubt anyone is particular about how it happens, per se, but it'd be good to just lay out basically every project nesting combination possible, make a decision about whether each one should be considered \"deno\" or \"not deno\", and then make sure the code passes.",
